    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="387"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 5, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1291.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to append hereto a copy of the
                        telegram<note n="1" xml:id="d387fn1">Printed ante, <ref target="#pg_299">p.
                            299</ref>.</note> in regard to the policy of the United States in China,
                    which was received yesterday morning, and which was at once communicated to
                    Baron von Richthofen (Count Bülow being with the Emperor at Wilhelmshaven) in
                    the form of a memorandum.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">And. D. White.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
